args:
Overprotective Louise remains unconvinced that
Lowen should be allowed to come along. She
then takes an injury while attempting to protect
him, which causes a fight between the siblings
and leaves new, complicated feelings floating
in her mind.
That takes care of the big one, but we still\nhave some smaller fiends to deal with.
Blast. Fighting this many is just going to\nlock us into a war of attrition.
If we keep shooting them one at a time,\nthis is never going to end!
Infuse my arrows, O twisting tempest!\nBecome a million whirlwinds that take\nthe lives of the wicked to the next life!
This technique is amazing! It gathers\nwind mana up and sends it flying into\nher enemies!
I've never seen so many foes dispatched\nat once. Truly we are in the company of\na master.
I need this kind of power if I want to\nprotect Lowen.
You're really going all-out to keep that\nkid safe, aren't you?
Still, he seems pretty good at taking care\nof himself, so maybe you can ease back\njust a little bit?
Don't be absurd! I refuse to allow Lowen\nto fight!
If something ever happened to my brother,\nI don't know what I'd do.
Louise, it's fine! I can protect myself!
No. I will protect you, and that is final.
I won't let you get so much as a scratch!
She really isn't listening to you, is she?
Yeah, but I'm pretty used to it. She never\ncares what I think when it comes to me.
...Fiends. There aren't many of them,\nso let's clear a path.
It dodged your attack. ...Lowen!\nIt's coming your way!
That's the last of them. Now show me the\nwound you took, Louise.
You have an odd definition of nothing.\nNow let me see it. ...Hmm. Oh dear.\nThis is certainly going to leave a scar.
Why did you even DO that, Louise?\nI totally could have handled that guy!
I said I'd protect you, and I did.
Why don't you listen to me...?
WHY DON'T YOU EVER FREAKING LISTEN\nTO ME?!
You can't protect me forever, you know!
Me and Luca'll go find the kid.\nYou guys set up camp, yeah?

O wind! Blowing over hill and dale
We ask this wish of you
May you protect the weak and frail
From evils old and new
And make my wish come true as well.\nPlease...
Ah. So this is where you were.
Oh, he eventually calmed down and fell\nasleep. But say, do you have a minute?
What was that song you were singing\njust now? It was beautiful.
That? It's a poem that's been passed down\nin our village for generations. We use it\nas a kind of prayer.
My mother taught it to me. It's one of\nthe only things I have left of her now.
Would you mind telling me more?\nAbout you and Lowen's family, that is.
There's really not much to tell.\nOur father died when I was very young.
After that, our mother brought my brother\nand I up on her own.
She was always prone to illness, but still\nworked herself to the bone to raise us.
In the end, however, she passed away and\nleft us on our own.
＂Take care of Lowen and be happy＂ were\nher last words to me.
I didn't have the time to cry about it;\nI was struggling to raise my brother.
I threw away everything about myself and\nfocused solely on him.
And that's why you're trying to protect him\nat any cost.
Yes, and I don't care if anyone else\nunderstands it or not. I will protect\nLowen, and I will do it my way.
You may not care what we all think,\nbut what about Lowen? I'd think he's\nearned at least some say in the matter.
We actually hadn't argued about it\nbefore today.
But listening to what he said, I wondered\nif maybe I've just been being acting like\nI have everything figured out.
I've been working so hard because I\nwant Lowen to be happy, and yet my\nwish is clearly unfulfilled.
You're going through a misunderstanding.\nIt happens.
Anyway, the wind has picked up, so we\nshould be going.
Tomorrow will be another challenging\nday, I'm sure.
For a whole host of reasons...
